Get recipes from GialloZafferano website

Source: R/get_recipes.R
get_recipes.Rd

This function gets several arguments from the user regarding the recipes they are looking for and scrapes GialloZafferano to obtain them. All of the arguments are optional. If the user does not pass any arguments, all the recipes of the website will be scraped.

Usage

get_recipes(
  category = "",
  difficulty = "",
  cooking_time = "",
  diet = "",
  ingredient = "",
  cooking_method = "",
  special = ""
)

Arguments

category

The recipe's category, as noted on the website

difficulty

The recipe's difficulty ("facile", "medio", "difficile")

cooking_time

The recipe's cooking time (15, 30 or 60 minutes)

diet

A healthy feature of the recipe (light, senza_glutine, senza_lattosio, vegetariano)

ingredient

A particular ingredient of the recipe (pesce, frutta, carne, formaggio)

cooking_method

The recipe's cooking method (al_forno, piatti_freddi, fritti)

special

A special category the recipe belongs to, selected by the website

Value

A dataframe with info about the recipes

Examples

get_recipes(category = "primi", difficulty = "facile")
